{"article_id":"vnhtfHWHieSsWU2J","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Employers are hiring at a restrained pace","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"as jitters about the economy linger .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"The U.S. economy added 175,000 jobs in May ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"according to the Department of Labor .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"Hiring at that rate is n't terrible ,","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"but it 's unexceptional at this point .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"It marks a slight improvement from April ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"when a revised 149,000 jobs were created ,","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"but still falls in line with average job growth over the last three years .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"Economists called it `` lackluster , '' `` par for the course , '' and `` unremarkable . '' `","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"` The U.S. labor market continues to recover .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"All in , the May report was decent but not fabulous , ''","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"said Jennifer Lee , senior economist with BMO Capital Markets .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"Revisions to March and April figures show","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"that the economy added 12,000 fewer jobs","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"than originally reported during those months .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"Even so , the May report was slightly stronger","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"than investors had expected ,","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"and stocks headed higher in morning trading .","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"Economists","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"surveyed by CNNMoney","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"had expected the report to show","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"158,000 jobs were added in May .","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"Meanwhile , the unemployment rate ticked up to 7.6 % from 7.5 % in April .","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"That minor rise came","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"as 420,000 people joined the labor force","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"-- an encouraging sign","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"that some formerly discouraged workers may be re-starting their job searches .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Businesses are citing concerns about the cost of health care reform rules ,","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"set to go into effect next year ,","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"as a major unknown","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"keeping them on the edge .","depth":6},{"id":32,"text":"`` Fear","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"of not knowing exactly what the rules are","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"is holding hiring back , ''","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"said John Silvia , Wells Fargo chief economist .","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"`` Once everybody knows the rules ,","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"they 'll all want to play the game . ''","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"Uncertainties also surround the broader economic impact from across-the-board government budget cuts","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"underway now ,","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"and weakness in foreign economies like China and Europe ,","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"which is subduing demand for U.S. goods and services abroad .","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"These concerns are leading firms to prefer temporary or part-time workers ,","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"said Scot Melland , CEO of Scot Melland , CEO of Dice Holdings","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"( DHX ) ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"a company","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"that runs several job search sites .","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"`` Companies have work","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"they still need to get done ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"but they do n't have enough confidence in the forward-look of their business","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"to make those full-time positions , ''","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"Indeed , the monthly jobs report showed a gain of 25,600 temporary jobs in May .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Restaurants and bars added 38,000 jobs .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"Other strong sectors for job growth included retail ,","depth":11},{"id":55,"text":"which added 28,000 jobs ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"and education and health services ,","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"which added 26,000 jobs .","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"Construction added 7,000 jobs ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"falling in line with other signs of an ongoing housing recovery .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Meanwhile , the federal government cut 14,000 jobs","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"and manufacturers cut 8,000 jobs .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"Overall , the U.S. economy lost 8.7 million jobs in the financial crisis ,","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"and has since gained back 6.3 million jobs .","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"The employment-population ratio was unchanged ,","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"showing","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"that 58.6 % of adults over age 16 have a job .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"That rate has barely budged over the last three years","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"-- and the last time","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"it was hovering so low","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"was 30 years ago .","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"Since job growth continued at a slow pace in May ,","depth":3},{"id":72,"text":"the newest data is unlikely to change the Federal Reserve 's current stimulus policies .","depth":3},{"id":73,"text":"The central bank is looking for `` substantial improvement '' in the job market","depth":3},{"id":74,"text":"before it starts winding down its controversial program","depth":4},{"id":75,"text":"of buying $ 85 billion in Treasuries and mortgage-backed securities each month .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":151,"left":146,"right":150,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":103,"right":145,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":77,"right":102,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":77,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":87,"right":101,"relation":"elabora